---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Pulmonary Nurses | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Pulmonary Nurses working internationally, covering respiratory care abroad, lung disease nursing, and global pulmonary nursing careers.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Pulmonary Nurses";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Pulmonary Nurses working abroad, providing respiratory care internationally, and building careers across pulmonary clinics, hospitals, and international respiratory centers.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/pulmonary-nurse-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/pulmonary-nurse-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Pulmonary Nurse Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Pulmonary Nurses specialize in caring for patients with respiratory conditions including COPD, asthma, pulmonary fibrosis, lung cancer, and other chronic and acute lung diseases. They manage complex respiratory therapies, provide patient education, and support patients through respiratory rehabilitation and chronic disease management.
      </p>
      <p>
        International pulmonary nursing opportunities exist as respiratory diseases affect millions globally. Air quality concerns, infectious respiratory diseases, and chronic lung conditions create demand for pulmonary expertise in international hospitals and global health organizations.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Pulmonary Nurses working abroad across pulmonary clinics, hospitals, and international respiratory centers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Pulmonary Nurses</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Professional liability', why: 'Respiratory therapy decisions', typical: 'Important consideration' },
          { need: 'Respiratory illness coverage', why: 'Airborne exposure risk', typical: 'Should be comprehensive' },
          { need: 'Infectious disease coverage', why: 'TB and respiratory pathogens', typical: 'Critical for pulmonary' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Chronic disease and end-of-life', typical: 'Important to include' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Career protection', typical: 'Review carefully' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Respiratory Exposure Risks</h3>
      <p>
        Pulmonary nursing involves exposure to respiratory pathogens including tuberculosis. Airborne transmission risks require vigilance. Comprehensive respiratory and infectious disease coverage essential.
      </p>
      <p>
        COVID-19 highlighted respiratory nursing exposure risks. Pandemic response creates additional demands. Understanding respiratory disease coverage important for pulmonary specialists.
      </p>

      <h3>Chronic Disease Management</h3>
      <p>
        Many pulmonary patients have progressive, incurable conditions. Managing patient decline and end-of-life care creates emotional demands. Mental health support valuable for sustainability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Pulmonology Practices</h3>
      <p>
        Physician pulmonology offices. Practice benefits vary. Outpatient respiratory care. Practices offer specialty environment.
      </p>

      <h3>Hospital Respiratory Services</h3>
      <p>
        Inpatient and ICU respiratory care. Hospital employee benefits. Acute respiratory management. Hospital settings offer comprehensive benefits.
      </p>

      <h3>Pulmonary Rehabilitation</h3>
      <p>
        Respiratory rehabilitation programs. Healthcare employer benefits. Functional recovery focus. Rehabilitation offers outcome focus.
      </p>

      <h3>Sleep Medicine</h3>
      <p>
        Sleep disorder centers. Healthcare employer benefits. Sleep apnea and disorders. Sleep medicine offers subspecialty.
      </p>

      <h3>International Respiratory Programs</h3>
      <p>
        Global pulmonary initiatives. International coverage essential. TB and respiratory health focus. International work offers global impact.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Pulmonary Nurses"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Pulmonary Nurses working abroad across pulmonary clinics, hospitals, and international respiratory centers."
      buttonText="Compare Pulmonary Nurse Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Clinical Foundation</h3>
      <p>
        Registered Nurse (RN) licensure required. Critical care or medical-surgical background valuable. Respiratory assessment skills. RN enables pulmonary specialization.
      </p>

      <h3>Pulmonary Certification</h3>
      <p>
        Certified Pulmonary Function Technologist collaboration. COPD Educator certification. Asthma educator credentials. Specialty credentials enhance practice.
      </p>

      <h3>Critical Care</h3>
      <p>
        CCRN for ICU pulmonary care. Ventilator management expertise. Respiratory failure management. Critical care skills valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Advanced Practice</h3>
      <p>
        Pulmonary nurse practitioner programs. Advanced prescriptive authority. Expanded scope of practice. Advanced practice widens opportunities.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Airborne Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        TB and respiratory pathogen risk. Aerosol-generating procedures. N95 and respiratory protection. Airborne exposure ongoing concern.
      </p>

      <h3>Pandemic Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Respiratory pandemic frontline. Surge capacity demands. PPE requirements intensive. Pandemic response demanding.
      </p>

      <h3>Chronic Disease Burden</h3>
      <p>
        Progressive disease management. Patient decline witnessed. End-of-life care involvement. Chronic disease emotionally demanding.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Patient positioning for procedures. Equipment management. Rehabilitation assistance. Physical demands present.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Assessment</h3>
      <p>
        Respiratory assessment expertise. Pulmonary function interpretation support. Oxygen saturation monitoring. Assessment guides treatment.
      </p>

      <h3>Therapy Management</h3>
      <p>
        Oxygen therapy administration. Inhaler and nebulizer education. Ventilator management when applicable. Therapy management essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Education</h3>
      <p>
        Disease self-management teaching. Inhaler technique instruction. Smoking cessation support. Education empowers patients.
      </p>

      <h3>Care Coordination</h3>
      <p>
        Respiratory therapy collaboration. Pulmonary rehabilitation referral. Home oxygen coordination. Coordination ensures continuity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>International Opportunities</h3>
      <p>
        Global respiratory disease burden. TB programs worldwide. Air quality health impact. Coverage must accommodate international practice.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Staff to program leadership. Advanced practice transition. Research and education. Multiple advancement paths.
      </p>

      <h3>Growing Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Respiratory disease prevalence increasing. Aging population needs. Environmental health impact. Strong future demand.
      </p>

      <h3>Subspecialization</h3>
      <p>
        COPD focus. Asthma specialty. Sleep medicine. Pulmonary oncology. Multiple subspecialty options.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a pulmonary nurse considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Respiratory disease burden varies globally. TB prevalent in many regions. Air quality impacts practice. Coverage should address respiratory exposures.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">How significant is TB exposure risk?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Varies by location and setting. Higher in endemic regions. TB testing and coverage important. Understanding exposure essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What certifications matter?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            COPD and asthma educator credentials. CCRN for ICU. Pulmonary rehabilitation training. Certifications enhance credibility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is chronic disease care emotionally demanding?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Progressive diseases challenging. Patient decline witnessed. Mental health support valuable. Emotional demands significant.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about pandemic response?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Respiratory nurses frontline. Surge demands significant. Coverage should address pandemic scenarios. Understanding expectations important.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is the career outlook positive?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Growing demand globally. Respiratory disease increasing. Environmental factors contributing. Positive future trajectory.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by understanding your employer's coverage provisions and respiratory protection protocols. Hospital and pulmonary clinic positions typically include benefits. Ensure infectious disease and TB coverage adequate. Consider mental health support for chronic disease management demands.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pulmonary Nurses provide specialized care for patients with respiratory conditions, managing complex therapies and supporting patients through chronic disease journeys. Your coverage should support this essential specialty—addressing respiratory exposure risks, enabling international opportunities, and protecting your health for sustained service.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Pulmonary Nursing Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Pulmonary Nurses working abroad across pulmonary clinics, hospitals, and international respiratory centers."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
